      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 48
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a concours-level example of naturally aspirated precision. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to reach a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. This chassis is mechanically sorted with a reinforced rear subframe, updated rod bearings, and a freshly serviced Getrag 6-speed manual transmission. The power is managed by a variable M differential lock, providing exceptional lateral grip and exit speeds. Finished in flawless Carbon Black over Nappa leather, the vehicle exhibits zero cowl shake or bushing deflection, maintaining its original factory geometry and damping characteristics. A turnkey investment for the purist.",
